  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nThis stacktrace is leaking out:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n   ERROR  07-14 10:49:23        peer  Unexpected error during auth/p2p handshake with <Node(0x391792dc9f4d695f8f3b8b577f1fcef611d554b8b1667bf4002ebad53bc4a452d00095141ca44bb97c0a7971dee39ec0fbaebd886a0ebdfa7c7e0d8bce2e07da@34.241.35.62:30303)>\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/peer.py\", line 808, in connect\r\n    self.vm_configuration, self.cancel_token))\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/cancel_token.py\", line 102, in wait\r\n    return await self.wait_first(awaitable, token=token, timeout=timeout)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/cancel_token.py\", line 124, in wait_first\r\n    return await wait_with_token(*awaitables, token=token_chain, timeout=timeout)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/cancel_token.py\", line 161, in wait_with_token\r\n    return done.pop().result()\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/peer.py\", line 138, in handshake\r\n    await peer.ensure_same_side_on_dao_fork(vm_configuration)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/peer.py\", line 212, in ensure_same_side_on_dao_fork\r\n    timeout=CHAIN_SPLIT_CHECK_TIMEOUT)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/cancel_token.py\", line 102, in wait\r\n    return await self.wait_first(awaitable, token=token, timeout=timeout)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/cancel_token.py\", line 124, in wait_first\r\n    return await wait_with_token(*awaitables, token=token_chain, timeout=timeout)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/cancel_token.py\", line 161, in wait_with_token\r\n    return done.pop().result()\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/peer.py\", line 668, in _get_headers_at_chain_split\r\n    cmd, msg = await self.read_msg()\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/peer.py\", line 368, in read_msg\r\n    decoded_msg = cast(Dict[str, Any], cmd.decode(msg))\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/protocol.py\", line 95, in decode\r\n    return self.decode_payload(data[1:])\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/sites/py-evm/p2p/protocol.py\", line 82, in decode_payload\r\n    data = rlp.decode(rlp_data, sedes=decoder)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/python-environments/evm/lib/python3.6/site-packages/rlp/codec.py\", line 213, in decode\r\n    item, end = consume_item(rlp, 0)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/python-environments/evm/lib/python3.6/site-packages/rlp/codec.py\", line 191, in consume_item\r\n    return consume_payload(rlp, s, t, l)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/python-environments/evm/lib/python3.6/site-packages/rlp/codec.py\", line 172, in consume_payload\r\n    item, next_item_start = consume_payload(rlp, s, t, l)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/python-environments/evm/lib/python3.6/site-packages/rlp/codec.py\", line 172, in consume_payload\r\n    item, next_item_start = consume_payload(rlp, s, t, l)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/python-environments/evm/lib/python3.6/site-packages/rlp/codec.py\", line 171, in consume_payload\r\n    t, l, s = consume_length_prefix(rlp, next_item_start)\r\n  File \"/Users/piper/python-environments/evm/lib/python3.6/site-packages/rlp/codec.py\", line 131, in consume_length_prefix\r\n    raise DecodingError('Encoded as short string although single byte was possible', rlp)\r\nrlp.exceptions.DecodingError: Encoded as short string although single byte was possible\r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nHaven't investigated yet\r\n",
